    <name>
      <text>Determining Real and Imaginary Parts of a Complex Function</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p></p><p></p><p>Find the real part \(u(x,y)\) and the imaginary part \(v(x,y)\) of the complex function \(f(z) = {@ f_z @}\).</p><p>\(u(x,y)\) = [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;</p><p>\(v(x,y)\) = [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>Find the real part \(u(x,y)\) and the imaginary part \(v(x,y)\) of the complex function \(f(z) =  \displaystyle {@ f_z @}\)</p>
<p>We have</p>
<p> \(\begin{align}
f(z) & = \displaystyle {@f_z@} \\
& = \displaystyle {@subst(x+y*%i,z,f_z)@} \quad (\text{by substituting } z=x+iy) \\
& = \displaystyle {@f_xy@}  \\
& = \displaystyle  {@ta1@}+ \left({@ta2@} \right){@%i@} \\
& = \displaystyle  {@ratsimp(ta1)@}+ \left({@ratsimp(ta2)@} \right){@%i@} \\
\end{align}\). </p>
<p> Since \(f(z)= u(x,y)+{@%i@} v(x,y) \), by identification, we have</p>
<p>\(u(x,y) =\displaystyle {@ratsimp(ta1)@}\) and \(v(x,y)=\displaystyle {@ratsimp(ta2)@}\).</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
